      <t>&lt;p&gt;The Dictionary Server Protocol (DICT) is a TCP transaction based query/response protocol that allows a client to access dictionary definitions from a set of natural language dictionary databases.  This memo provides information for the Internet community.  It does not specify an Internet standard of any kind.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
